<h2><a name="TOC-The-five-steps-within-the-risk-management-procedure"></a>The five steps within the risk management procedure</h2>
<span style="width:60%"><img alt="risk management procedure - identify, assess, plan, implement, communicate" src="/public/RISK_MANAGEMENT_PROCEDURE.png" style="width:60%;float:right" title="risk management procedure - identify, assess, plan, implement, communicate"></span>
<div style="background-color:transparent"><span style="background-color:transparent;font-size:1em;line-height:1.5">The five steps within the risk management procedure are:</span></div>
<div>
<ul><li><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,0)">Identify</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,0)">Assess</span></li>
<li><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,0)">Plan</span></li>
<li style="background-color:transparent">Implement</li>
<li style="background-color:transparent">Communicate</li></ul>
<div><span style="background-color:transparent">All of the above are on-going and the process is iterative. The </span><span style="background-color:rgb(255,255,0)">highlighted ones are called risk analysis</span>.</div>
</div>
<div style="background-color:transparent"><br>
</div>
<h3 style="background-color:transparent"><a name="TOC-IDENTIFY"></a>IDENTIFY</h3>
<h4 style="background-color:transparent"><a name="TOC-Context"></a>Context</h4>
<div style="background-color:transparent">In the Initiation stage the <a href="#TOC-RISK-MANAGEMENT-STRATEGY">Risk Management Strategy</a> identifies the context for risk management - the <b>HOW</b> and also <b>WHAT</b> it is that is at risk (not the risks).</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<h4 style="background-color:transparent"><a name="TOC-Risks"></a>Risks</h4>
<div style="background-color:transparent">Identify EACH risk. This can be done in workshops and perhaps using PESTLE. This process identifies a list of possible risks or can come from team members at any time during the project. Brainstorming, checklists etc can be used to help identify risks.</div>
<div style="background-color:transparent"><br>
</div>
<div style="background-color:transparent">For each risk identified, as it is identified, it should comprise of the <b>cause</b> of the risk, the <b>event</b> pertaining to the risk we are concerned with and the <b>effect</b> that this event would have on the project.It should be noted, as well, whether the risk is considered an opportunity or a threat.</div>
