<h2><a name="TOC-The-purpose-of-a-risk-budget"></a>The purpose of a risk budget</h2>
<div>A risk budget is there to provide the funding for both the management and the response actions of risks with a project.<br>
</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<h2><a name="TOC-The-probability-impact-and-proximity-of-a-risk"></a>The probability, impact and proximity of a risk</h2>
<div>A risk is measured by the <b>probability</b> and <b>impact</b>. The <b>proximity</b> is used to determine if a threat or opportunity is even a risk to the project at all or, if so, what the &nbsp;impact will be on <b>when</b> it occurs.</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div><span style="color:rgb(88,63,111);font-family:Palatino,Palatino Linotype,serif;font-size:1.5em;background-color:transparent;line-height:1.5">PROBABILITY</span></div>
<div>This is the <b>evaluated (quantified and considered) likelihood</b> &nbsp;of a particular threat or opportunity actually happening, including a consideration of the frequency with which this may arise (think flooding).</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<h3><a name="TOC-IMPACT"></a>IMPACT</h3>
<div>The <b>result of a particular threat or opportunity</b> actually occurring, or the anticipation of such a result. The impact will depend on the proximity. The ice age will come again no doubt but nothing to do with this project probably.</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<h3><a name="TOC-PROXIMITY"></a>PROXIMITY</h3>
<div>The time factor of risk, ie <b>when the risk may occur</b>. The impact of a risk might vary in severity depending on <b>when</b> the risk occurs. Time spans should be categorised in the <a href="#TOC-RISK-MANAGEMENT-STRATEGY">Risk Management Strategy</a>. Also timespans not relevant to this project should be stated e.g. over ten years ignore risk.</div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div><i>(If a competitor product is released six months prior to ours then we will suffer x amount but if they release one week ahead of ours then we will suffer less and perhaps actually gain from the publicity around this kind of product.)</i></div>
<div><br>
</div>
<div>
<div><b>Threat</b> - the general election will happen before I have passed my politician exam</div>
<div><b>Opportunity</b> - the general election will happen after I have passed my politician exam.</div>
</div>
<div><b>No risk</b> - I have now failed my politician exam and so the election does not matter any more.</div>
